com.pipe42.data

Class PojoConstructor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pipe42.data.PojoConstructor

  • public class PojoConstructor
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the facade for our POJO objects. Use the methods below to construct the various data object rather than doing it elsewhere or things like datetime and various validity checks will fail.
    Since:
    0.1.0
    See Also:
    Data

      • buildProjectObject

        public Project buildProjectObject(java.lang.String projectName,
                                  java.lang.String projectPrefix,
                                  java.lang.String ownerID,
                                  java.lang.String engineID,
                                  java.lang.String appID,
                                  java.lang.String projectNotes,
                                  java.lang.String folderTemplate,
                                  java.lang.String folderPath)
        Puts together the Project object for further use elsewhere. This particular method assumes that you want a brand new Project object with a new unique ID. If looking just to update an existing object, see updateProjectObject().
        Parameters:
        projectName - name of project
        projectPrefix - project prefix
        ownerID - owner ID
        engineID - renderengine ID
        appID - application ID
        projectNotes - project notes and comments
        Returns:
        a Project object

      • updateProjectObject

        public Project updateProjectObject(java.lang.String id,
                                   java.lang.String projectName,
                                   java.lang.String projectPrefix,
                                   java.lang.String ownerID,
                                   java.lang.String engineID,
                                   java.lang.String appID,
                                   java.lang.String projectNotes,
                                   java.lang.String folderTemplate,
                                   java.lang.String folderPath,
                                   java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> creationTime)
        This method assumes an existing Project object thus keeping project ID intact and just adding the time of modification into the output object. If you are after creating a brand new unique Project object, see buildProjectObject():
        Parameters:
        id - unique ID of this project
        projectName - name of project
        projectPrefix - project prefix
        ownerID - owner ID
        engineID - renderengine ID
        appID - application ID
        projectNotes - project notes and comments
        folderTemplate - the name of the template
        folderPath - the absolute path to the root of the project folders
        creationTime - time of initial creation
        Returns:
        a Project object
